Sun Position and Shadow Analysis for Timestamp Estimation
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Calculate sun positions using astronomical algorithms for any location and time
Analyze shadow patterns in images to extract directional information
Correlate shadow characteristics with solar positioning data
Estimate photograph timestamps using shadow analysis techniques
Apply these techniques for digital forensics and OSINT investigations
Prerequisites
Basic Python programming skills
Understanding of coordinate systems (latitude/longitude)
Familiarity with image analysis concepts
Basic trigonometry knowledge (angles, ratios)
Linux command line experience
